name: Google I/O17 Casablanca Extended

venue.name: New Work Lab
venue.address_1: 17 Rue Najib Mahfoud, 3rd Floor, Place Ollier, Quartier Gauthier Casablanca

description:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iZBWVwoJaJs

Hey everyone!

We have the pleasure and the honor to inform you that we will organize our next event in casablanca and we would love to see you there.

So what is Google I/O?

Google I/O (simply I/O) is an annual developer conference held by Google in San Francisco, California. I/O showcases technical in-depth sessions focused on building web, mobile, and enterprise applications with Google and open sources such as Android, Chrome and Chrome OS, APIs, Google Web Toolkit, App Engine, and more.

But the title of our event is I/O extended, so what is I/O extended?

I/O Extended events include a variety of options for developers from live streaming sessions to local demos, hackathons, codelabs, and more.

So let's not waste time on definitions, our event will contain these activities:

• Tech Talk about new technologies announced in the IO of this year

• Kotlin demo

• Workshop with experts about G suite et GCP

• Women Tech Makers (WTM) activity 

• Watching some of the live streaming

And you can contact us any time if you are interested to animate Workshop or give a talk about any technologie or anything to share with the community you are welcome.

You will found the recap of the Google IO 17 in the officiel website:  https://events.google.com/io/recap

let's live the experience in our city !! :D

Our speakers :

   DevFest Casablanca has two tracks wich contain : conferences, tech talks, workshops, codelabs.

name: Cloud Study Jam 2018 - Session 1
description:
• Where ?

link from google maps : https://www.google.com/maps/place/Université+Hassan+2+(Annexe)
Near of Bachkou tram station Direction Les Facultés, and in front of Club Pacha.

• I have a question.
Ask us any question in our facebook page https://www.facebook.com/GDGCasa/

• What we'll do
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?
Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Together we'll work through three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs, then you will get free access to the next quest so you can finish this series of labs at home to get a Google-hosted badge for your online profile. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Docker, Kubernetes and Scientific Data Processing, which will earn you additional badges.
Join this meetup to get official Google training, a $70+ value, free of charge.
Bring a laptop (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

Agenda:

2:00pm: presentation and Introduction of basics
2:30pm: Three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs
4:00pm: Break
4:30pm: Intro to Docker
6:00pm: Event ends

• What to bring
laptop
extension cord if possible !

• Important to know
Join this meetup to get official Google training, a $70+ value, free of charge.

name: Build Actions for Your Community! - Part I

venue.name: ENSAM Casablanca
venue.address_1: 150 Avenue Nile Sidi Othman Casablanca, Maroc 20700

description:
Introduction
Google-supported event to let developers learn how to build Apps for the Google Assistant that are useful for their community - whether it's a professional network, interest group, or their hometown.
The “Build Actions for Your Community” event is targeted at all levels of developers and we hope to see some great Actions on Google come out as a result and all of you have a ton of fun exploring what you can do with Google Assistant. We’ll provide you with content to learn how to create and actually build Actions on Google. They will be featured online and may even be showcased at the Google I/O Community Lounge.

9h - 10h Registration
10h:00 Welcome
10h:10 Building Conversational Experiences
10h:40 Conversational Design
11h:10 Coffee Break

11h:35 Lunch
13h:30 Creating your own Actions for the Google Assistant
15h:30 Feedback on the Actions on Google Platform
16h:10 Demos of your Actions
16h:50 Wrap Up

We will be waiting for you to explore together the Google Assistant actions.

#GoogleAssistant

Your laptops !

name: Build Actions for Your Community! - Part 2
description:
* Introduction
Welcome dear GDG & WTM Casablanca community,
This time Google supported event to let developers learn how to build Apps for the Google Assistant that are useful for our community - whether it's a professional network, interest group, or their hometown.
The “Build Actions for Your Community” event is targeted at all levels of developers and we hope to see some great Actions on Google come out as a result and all of you have a ton of fun exploring what you can do with Google Assistant. We’ll provide you with content to learn how to create and actually build Actions on Google. They will be featured online and may even be showcased at the Google I/O Community Lounge.

Also, we have a very special speaker, he is a Google Developer expert sir Mohamed Guendouz, our speaker is a very passionate Android developer. He is also an active member and organizer at GDG SBA, he enjoys organizing tech events and loves to speak at them to support his local community and helps local developers through meetings, hangouts, and blogs. He also helps some Algerian startups in their projects by coaching and helping them in developing their Android apps.
Currently, Mohamed is preparing a Ph.D. thesis on Big Data and Social Networks Analysis. He published some research papers in several international conferences and journals.
you can check their profile: https://developers.google.com/experts/people/mohamed-guendouz

* Agenda
09h:00 Registration
10h:00 Welcome
10h:20 Building Conversational Experiences & Conversational Design
11h:00 Coffee Break
11h:15 Discover Google Assistant & DialogFlow
11h:50 Codelab: Build a conversational App
13h:00 Lunch
14h:00 Creating your own Actions for the Google Assistant
16h:00 Feedback on the Actions on Google Platform
16h:30 Demos of your Actions
17h:10 Wrap Up
17h:20 event ends - Networking

* Tags: #buildactions #GoogleAssistant #GDGCasablanca #WTMCAsablanca

* Don't forget your Laptop !!

* Important
Free access, lunch not included

name: Google Developer Community : Next '18 Extended - Casablanca
description:
Join us for this year's Next Extended event, where we'll bring together cloud enthusiasts and the developer community to be a part of the Next '18 experience.

This year, we will be diving deep into cloud with technical keynotes, a hands-on TOPIC (Kubernetes, ML, or Google Cloud Certification) lab, and local speakers.

As an attendee, you'll not only be a part of our vibrant cloud community but also receive free access to Qwiklabs (a $55+ value)!

Don't forget to bring a laptop (PC, Mac, or Chromebook), and get ready for the best Next Extended yet!

Make sure to RSVP to receive upcoming information about this event, and visit https://cloudnext.withgoogle.com/ to learn more about Google Cloud Next '18.

name: Get hands-on with Cloud Study Jams
description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with Kubernetes Advanced.
Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

Agenda:

2:00pm: Opening & Check in
3:00pm: presentation and Introduction of basics
4:00pm: GCP Essentials labs, first lab about Kubernetes advanced
5:30pm: Coffee Break
